                          \
    Cowboy Bebop. Just this name will make anime haters cower in fear. Cowboy Bebop is one of these show you can call a \"classic\", something that transcends time and space, and, even after 16 years, be one of the best anime of all time.  \
Let's jam !\
Story 9/10\
Cowboy Bebop could be described as an episodic show, where all the episodes are standalones. But  this isn't really accurate. Some episodes, such as the fifth and last one, follow a linear story, and the \"standalone\" ones are mostly here to develop the characters and setting, in a brilliant way. Each one of these episodes is\
          \
        a little gem of its own, and deserves to be appreciated. \
Art 10/10\
This show is just... amazing. When you consider that Bebop was one of the last big animes not using digital animation, and it is still beautifully animated, even by today's standards, well... That alone says it all.\
Sound 10/10\
People, this is Yoko Kanno. What did you expect ? For those who don't know who Yoko Kanno is, you'll discover it soon enough. Cowboy Bebop just lives for music. If you took out the action and space setting, all you'd find would be music. Everything, from the episode names to some characters, everything is a musical easter egg. Therefore, the soundtrack of this show is undoubtedly one of the best I've ever heard, from the amazing opening to the wonderful ending.\
Characters 9/10\
What can be said about the characters ? They're just so great. Their development is one of the best I've ever seen, being subtle yet amazing, hinted yet memorable. The three main characters, Spike, Faye and Jet are all different, and awfully realistic. They are understandable and lovable. On the other hand, the secondary characters, which you usually only see for an episode or two are also outstanding. In only 20 minutes, you get to know them as well as the main cast, while still having the plot go on.\
But, as many things go, there is a flaw. And this flaw is Ed. I have to confess, I've never seen a main character so empty since the first season of Aldnoah; Zero. If Ed had not been there, the characters would have deserved a 10. But don't worry, this doesn't kill any of the enjoyment, because Ed is mostly here for comical relief, and does its job well.\
Enjoyment 10/10\
While some people describe Cowboy Bebop as slow, which killed the enjoyment, I have to disagree. After all, it is an episodic show for the most part, and the pacing \"suffers\" from it. But nevertheless, I hugely enjoyed watching Cowboy Bebop, and loved every minute of it.\
Overall 10/10\
There are many shows whose dream is to become the perfect anime, sometime being close to achieving it, sometimes not. But Bebop must be one of the closest one to perfection. \
I highly recommend you to watch this anime, even at the price of your own life. Because bebop isn't your random anime. It's one of the few shows who can pretend to be called a finished work of art. \
If you enjoyed ( or not) reading this review, don't hesitate to send me a message to discuss this wonderful anime.\
See you, space cowboy ! \
