STORY (Concept 4.5/5, Development 4.5/5)\
The concept is rather cliche. Future technology in combination with the Big Wild West and Jazzy feel. \
This doesn't mean it is not good. History\
          \
        shows how copying good stuff is always good. And the idea of \"Space Cowboy\" is simply cool and awesome. \
By definition, filler episodes are episodes that are just there without any connection to the purpose of the anime. What makes cowboy bebop amazing is that its fillers have purposes. \
As a person who greatly criticizes on Black Butler and Darker than Black's episodic storyline, I cannot do the same to Cowboy. \
Unlike Black Butler, every little episodes in Cowboy is extremely interesting, which means, NOT boring. In Cowboy most if not all episodes stand strong on their own, so the connections they have with the main plot are clear and meaningful. \
Unlike Darker than Black, the main characters of the show stays as the main characters. So all arcs have Spike, Jet, Faye and Ed as the center of the plot. \
All the characters have their own episodes. These episodes are scatters all over the place so we the viewers can change the flavor once in a while.  \
My main problem with the show is that, I don't have the motivation to go to the next episodes... I guess that's just me. \
The ending is awesome.\
All in all, this is how you do episodic show. I respect it despite the fact I don't like episodic show. They deserve the credit of making all the episodes interesting. \
\
CHARACTERS (Design 5/5, Development 5/5)\
As I said previously, all the characters have their own background and development. \
The Bebop Crew consists of Spike the Cowboy, Faye the hotty, Jet the daddy, Ed the kid and Ein the dog. \
Spike is probably the most interesting cowboy in all of existence. For a lack of better term, he is a serious person, yet a troll. He is super positive, he is a likable person who is supposed to be the \"Bang\" on the ship. He died once, which adds layers and layers of mystery on top of this badass cowboy. As the show unfolds, his past is resolved...\
Faye and Jet are also very interesting. Like spike, they find Bebop their new home and abandoned their past. Unlike Spike, they are truly able to abandon their history and reborn. Spike is different from the rest of the crew because he cannot run away, or he choose to not run away. \
Ed doesn't really have any personally background. She is a fun little character that infuses herself with the Bebop. She has her place in the show and I think the way they present it is great.\
Ein is the best dog in the history of humanity. Period. \
\
GRAPHIC (Art 5/5 Animation 5/5)\
The art is godlike. They are so gorgeous. The space scenes and the different planets are mind blowing. Characters are also very well designed. \
Let's just put it this way so people would not run away because \"old animations suck\". \
Cowboy Bebop has 1998 animation that is better than the majority of the 2018 animations. The pictures are literally drawn BY HAND, FRAME BY FRAME. I could not believe my eyes when I stepped in to the episode. They are simply so smooth and detailed. The only time when you would see something that's recycled is when the spaceships take off. Action scenes are awesome. \
The only thing I can say that is not appealing is that I watched a 4:3 series on a 16/9 screen. :/\
