    Cowboy Bebop, hardly more needs to be said. It's a one-of-a-kind show, and a cornerstone of its culture.\
Phenomenal story, excellent characters, scripting, and voice acting, and a uniqueness that sets it apart from everything else. Every detail of this show feels original and real, although it's difficult to qualify, if I'm being honest.\
Cowboy Bebop takes all of that, and wisely uses it to show off their incredibly deep and thorough characters. Each of them is  a fully flushed out and real character that has their own reasons for being where they are. All of the voice acting is phenomenal, showing off the excellent scripting.\
          \
         Each character's backstory is fairly thoroughly explained, the two primary protagonists especially so. This gives the setting an added layer of depth, in my opinion, one that is often forgotten in modern day media. Each character's story is unique and moving in its own way.\
But still, this show takes all that even, and somehow makes it special. It's that indescribable feeling that some shows have, that just make them stand out to you; a fleeting and haunting feeling that passes over as you finish the last episode, because you realize it was always going to end this way, just as the main protagonist realized too. \
The only thing holding this show back from being a 10/10 is the middle of the season, where things get a little stale. Filler took up space where I wanted exposition and story, and while it may have helped to develop the main characters somewhat and served to provide space for production of the real episodes to be fully fleshed out, I think that these fillers didn't add enough to justify their presence. If these episodes were removed or reformatted, and the main story kept more concise, then this show would have easily been a 10/10, and have a spot in my Legends.\
But despite all that, this show is still one of the best anime's existing, and again is a cornerstone of its kind. There's no other show like it out there, and it's 100% worth the watch.\
9/10\
